
[1]obloquy

   OB'LOQUY, n. [L. obloquor; ob and loquor, to speak.]

   1. Censorious speech; reproachful language; language that casts
   contempt on men or their actions.

   Shall names that made your city the glory of the earth, be mentioned
   with obloquy and detraction?

   2. Cause of reproach; disgrace. [Not used.]
